law.catch_line: Deposit of fees in agency fund.
law.text: All fees imposed and collected under the provisions of this chapter shall be paid to the secretary-treasurer of the board for the use of the board, and shall be deposited in the State Treasury to the credit of an agency fund for the use of the board.
law.history: Created 1954 Ky. Acts ch. 27, sec. 15, effective June 17, 1954.
